index;<br />&gt; -               if (alloc_set_pte(vmf, page))<br />&gt; -                       goto unlock;<br />&gt; +               if (pte_none(*vmf-&gt;pte))<br />&gt; +                       do_set_pte(vmf, page);<br />&gt; +               /* no need to invalidate: a not-present page won't be cached */<br />&gt; +               update_mmu_cache(vma, vmf-&gt;address, vmf-&gt;pte);<br />&gt;                 unlock_page(head);<br />&gt; -               goto next;<br />&gt; +               continue;<br /><br />This can't be right.<br /><br />Look at what happens if "pte_none()" is not true.. It won't install<br />the new pte, but it also won't drop the ref to the page.<br /><br />So I think it needs to be<br /><br />-               if (alloc_set_pte(vmf, page))<br />+               if (!pte_none(*vmf-&gt;pte))<br />                        goto unlock;<br />+               do_set_pte(vmf, page);<br /><br />instead, so that the "if somebody else already filled the page table"<br />case gets handled right.<br /><br />Hmm?<br /><br />              Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
